                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.547,
                                "byte_start": 87502,
                                "byte_stop": 125745,
                                "text": "The opinion of the court No. 00-927, Chao, Secretary of Labor versus Mallard Bay Drilling will be announced by Justice Stevens."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.547,
                        "stop": 228.519,
                        "byte_start": 125745,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15060,
                            "name": "John Paul Stevens",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/john_paul_stevens",
                            "last_name": "Stevens",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2704,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 188200800,
                                    "date_end": 1277787600,
                                    "appointing_president": "Gerald Ford",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2704"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32732,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 62101,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/john_paul_stevens.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 12611,
                            "identifier": "john_paul_stevens"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.547,
                                "stop": 14.651,
                                "byte_start": 125745,
                                "byte_stop": 146121,
                                "text": "This case comes to us from the United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.651,
                                "stop": 25.149,
                                "byte_start": 146121,
                                "byte_stop": 188126,
                                "text": "It involves an oil and gas exploration barge known as Rig 52 which belongs to the respondent, Mallard Bay Drilling."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 25.149,
                                "stop": 33.909,
                                "byte_start": 188126,
                                "byte_stop": 223234,
                                "text": "While its crew was drilling a well in the territory of waters of Louisiana, Rig 52 exploded as a result of a gas leak."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 33.909,
                                "stop": 37.525,
                                "byte_start": 223234,
                                "byte_stop": 237654,
                                "text": "Four members of the crew were killed and two were injured."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 37.525,
                                "stop": 45.079,
                                "byte_start": 237654,
                                "byte_stop": 267851,
                                "text": "The United States Coast Guard investigated the incident but did not accused Mallard Bay of violating any Coast Guard Regulations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.079,
                                "stop": 60.743,
                                "byte_start": 267851,
                                "byte_stop": 330545,
                                "text": "The coast guard\u2019s report explained its limits however by noting that Rig 52 was an uninspected vessel as opposed to an inspected vessel, which meant that the barge was not comprehensively regulated by the Coast Guard."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 60.743,
                                "stop": 72.724,
                                "byte_start": 330545,
                                "byte_stop": 378402,
                                "text": "Based largely on information from the guard\u0027s report, the Occupational Safety and Health Administration cited Mallard Bay for three violations of the Occupational Safety and Health Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.724,
                                "stop": 89.156,
                                "byte_start": 378402,
                                "byte_stop": 444230,
                                "text": "In the OSHA administered proceeding, Mallard Bay challenge OSHA\u2019s jurisdiction to issue this citations, arguing that the guard possess exclusive statutory authority to regulate occupational safety and health standards on vessels in navigable waters."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.156,
                                "stop": 97.282,
                                "byte_start": 444230,
                                "byte_stop": 476726,
                                "text": "The Administrative Law Judge rejected the challenge and assessed the penalty against Mallard Bay for its violations of the Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.282,
                                "stop": 113.329,
                                "byte_start": 476726,
                                "byte_stop": 540883,
                                "text": "The Fifth Circuit reversed holding that the Coast Guard possessed exclusive jurisdiction over working conditions of board vessels such as Rig 52, thereby precluding OSHA from applying its regulations to both inspected and uninspected vessels."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.329,
                                "stop": 121.72,
                                "byte_start": 540883,
                                "byte_stop": 574424,
                                "text": "Because other Courts of Appeals had not endorsed such extensive pre-emption of OSHA\u2019s regulation, we granted certiorari to resolve the conflict."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 121.72,
                                "stop": 129.067,
                                "byte_start": 574424,
                                "byte_stop": 603786,
                                "text": "We reversed the decision below and conclude that OSHA had jurisdiction to issue the citations against Mallard Bay."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 129.067,
                                "stop": 146.022,
                                "byte_start": 603786,
                                "byte_stop": 671600,
                                "text": "The statute bars OSHA from regulating working conditions \u201cwith respect to which other federal agencies exercise statutory authority to prescribe or enforce standards or regulations affecting occupational safety and health.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 146.022,
                                "stop": 157.483,
                                "byte_start": 671600,
                                "byte_stop": 717471,
                                "text": "Whether OSHA\u2019s jurisdiction is preempted in a given case thus depends on whether another federal agency has exercise its authority to regulate the working conditions in questions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.483,
                                "stop": 174.005,
                                "byte_start": 717471,
                                "byte_stop": 783613,
                                "text": "As its language of the statute makes clear, mere possession by another agency of unexercised authorities is not enough to displace OSHA\u2019s jurisdiction, nor is another federal agencies minimal exercise of authority with respect to a limited class of working conditions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 174.005,
                                "stop": 183.72,
                                "byte_start": 783613,
                                "byte_stop": 822483,
                                "text": "The parties do not dispute that the Coast Guards comprehensive regulation of inspected vessels has preempted OSHA\u2019s authority to regulate those vessels."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 183.72,
                                "stop": 192.312,
                                "byte_start": 822483,
                                "byte_stop": 856756,
                                "text": "However, concerning uninspected vessels like Rig 52, the Coast Guards Regulatory Authority is much more limited."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 192.312,
                                "stop": 200.438,
                                "byte_start": 856756,
                                "byte_stop": 889357,
                                "text": "In this case, the working conditions that were the subject of OSHA\u2019s citations related to inland drilling operations on uninspected vessels."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 200.438,
                                "stop": 210.696,
                                "byte_start": 889357,
                                "byte_stop": 930317,
                                "text": "Because the Coast Guard has neither affirmatively regulated such working conditions nor asserted comprehensive regulatory jurisdiction over them and uninspected vessels."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 210.696,
                                "stop": 214.717,
                                "byte_start": 930317,
                                "byte_stop": 946408,
                                "text": "The Coast Guard has not exercised its preemptive authority."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 214.717,
                                "stop": 222.033,
                                "byte_start": 946408,
                                "byte_stop": 975665,
                                "text": "As a result, the jurisdiction is not preempted and as I say we reversed the judgment of the Court of Appeal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 222.033,
                                "stop": 228.519,
                                "byte_start": 975665,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Except for Justice Scalia who did not participate in the decision, our opinion is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
